<h3>Question 12</h3>
<div><p><p>Write short notes on (any two):<br />
a. Digital analog simulator<br />
b. Simulation tools</p</p></div><div><strong>Answer:</strong><br><style>body .mathjax_wrap{width: 100%;overflow-x: scroll;margin-bottom:10px;}</style><p><strong>a. Digital analog simulator</strong></p>
<p>It is a tool used  in simulation and modeling to comprehensively study systems that blend digital and analog components. It indicate the use of programming language in digital computers to simulate the continuous system.</p>
<p>The language is composed of macro-instructions which are able to act as added, integrator and sign changer. A program is written to link these macro instructions as per the necessity.</p>
<p>It allows users to create virtual models of electronic circuits or systems that consist of elements such as resistors, capacitors, transistors, digital logic gates, and more.Users can analyze the simulated circuits using various tools provided by the simulator.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><strong>b. Simulation tools</strong></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Simulation tool is a software which is used for simulating the hardware, software and network. It is a type of software based on the process of modeling a real world phenomenon with mathematical formula. This program allows the users to observe the operation without actually performing the operation. Its main importance is : how it actually supports the model building.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The tools commonly used in simulation are :</p>
<ul style="list-style-type: square;">
<li>Processor simulation</li>
<li>Memory Simulation</li>
<li>ALU simulation</li>
<li>Logic Network simulation</li>
<li>CPU Network simulation</li>
</ul>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
</div>
